Subject: Re: [T2] Pedal problem

> The next day I took the pedal assembly apart and found that the 30 year old
> grease had dried out and solidified causing the problem.  A good cleaning
> and lubrication fixed the problem for me too.  I guess the moral of the
> story is to not over look the simple things when there's a problem.

Even if there isn't a noticable problem, I recommend regreasing all
the pedals and the shifter mechanism if you haven't yet.

Here's what my shifter looked like:
http://www.donimages.com/guac/images/shifter1/parts-shiftplatecompare.jpg
http://www.donimages.com/guac/images/shifter1/shift-before03.jpg

There was no useful grease in there.

